        <strong>Wild-Harvested vs Pool-Grown</strong>
        <p>Wild-harvested sea moss absorbs minerals from natural ocean water, potentially providing a richer mineral profile than pool-grown (cultivated) sea moss grown in controlled environments. Look for "wild-harvested," "wildcrafted," or "ocean-grown" on the label. Pool-grown moss is not necessarily inferior but may have a different mineral composition.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>Heavy Metal Testing</strong>
        <p>Seaweed can bioaccumulate heavy metals (lead, mercury, arsenic, cadmium) from ocean water. Always choose sea moss gummies that are third-party tested for heavy metal contamination. Reputable brands provide certificates of analysis verifying that heavy metal levels fall below established safety thresholds.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
